  "texts": [
    "Let C be a finite region and let S, S ′ ∈ Bd(Σ C) be distinct boundary components.",
    "Then we have t S (a)t S ′ (b) = t S ′ (b)t S (a), for all a ∈ Tube S and all b ∈ Tube S ′.",
    "In particular, all B f projectors commute with one another.Proof: Let C S and C S ′ be the collar regions of the boundary components S and S ′ and put C = C S ∪ C S ′.",
    "Then S and S ′ are also boundary components of Σ C with the same corresponding Tube-representations t S and t S ′.",
    "We regard t S (a) and t S ′ (b) as operators on H C. On the subspace H C ⊂ H C, commutativity of t S (a) and t S ′ (b) now follows from Proposition 4.4 and the fact that Tube-actions corresponding to different boundary components on the skein module A(Σ C) all commute with each other."
